<paragraph id="9338D715A85232EC61D34653643EB701" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Additional description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="34C9210F2E33E9C3C7A17EDB067B77AF" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">
The colour of the pronotum, elytra, and legs are variable in this species (Figs 
<figureCitation id="8273D7204A698D7024FAC5823D3DB9B6" captionStart="Figures 13–22" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figures 13 - 22. Habitus of Tillicera species 13 Tillicera michaeli 14 T. obscura 15 T. paula 16, 17 T. pseudocleroides 18, 19 T. sensibilis 20 T. soror 21 T. tonkinensis 22 T. wenii. Scale bars 2 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1095.80097.figures13-22" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/672266" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">16</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="721ADA92725F55577B9A8E05BA20D3E7" captionStart="Figures 13–22" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figures 13 - 22. Habitus of Tillicera species 13 Tillicera michaeli 14 T. obscura 15 T. paula 16, 17 T. pseudocleroides 18, 19 T. sensibilis 20 T. soror 21 T. tonkinensis 22 T. wenii. Scale bars 2 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1095.80097.figures13-22" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/672266" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">17</figureCitation>
). Antennomeres V-X with an area vested with sensilla basiconica at the apical margin in ventral view.
</paragraph>
